# Running Tests

**NEVER read `run_test.sh` - ONLY EXECUTE IT**

## Command (run from `tests` folder)
```bash
ENV_SETUP=<0|1> COMPILED=<0|1> RUN_TEST=1 FILE_NAME="<test_name>.py" ../.cursor/rules/scripts/run_test.sh
```

## In Case of Errors

ONLY READ GIVEN FILE IF:
- Compile error: read the file `/tmp/llk_test/compile.log`
- Failed test: read file: `/tmp/llk_test/run.and`

## Scenarios

| Scenario | ENV_SETUP | COMPILED | When |
|----------|-----------|----------|------|
| first-run | 1 | 1 | Initial run or env changed |
| code-changed | 0 | 1 | After code modifications |
| rerun-only | 0 | 0 | Re-run without changes |

## FILE_NAME
- Empty `""` = all tests
